04:19.100 --> 04:20.200
"The Conners" is recorded

04:20.209 --> 04:22.120
in front of a live studio audience.

04:22.340 --> 04:23.920
Just broke up with Neil.

04:23.960 --> 04:26.000
Ohh. How'd he take it?

04:26.160 --> 04:28.670
Uh, he was devastated

04:28.700 --> 04:30.940
until I told him that he wasn't.

04:32.920 --> 04:35.709
I can't believe I was about to
make the same mistake again.

04:35.710 --> 04:37.719
Well, it's never too late to change.

04:37.720 --> 04:40.580
I've found that vocalizing
my feelings really helps.

04:40.600 --> 04:44.800
Last night, I suggested that
Peter might want to get a job,

04:45.020 --> 04:48.690
and he started packing his bags,

04:48.790 --> 04:51.360
and I decided to vocalize

04:51.460 --> 04:54.260
that I would do anything if he stayed,

04:54.270 --> 04:55.970
and he stayed!

04:58.900 --> 05:01.020
That just seems like desperation.

05:01.060 --> 05:04.040
Mm. To the untrained eye.

05:09.160 --> 05:11.380
I could use a laugh. What's that?

05:11.420 --> 05:12.830
I needed something to read, so I grabbed

05:12.850 --> 05:14.120
the new edition of Lock 'Em Up

05:14.220 --> 05:16.150
off the counter at the AM-PM.

05:16.250 --> 05:19.219
Ah, nothing says "fine literature"

05:19.220 --> 05:21.980
like the counter at the AM-PM.

05:22.140 --> 05:23.430
No, it's a hoot.

05:23.530 --> 05:25.176
They print the mug shots
of all the arrests

05:25.200 --> 05:27.030
in Lanford every month.

05:27.130 --> 05:29.630
This woman shot her
mother in her garage.

05:29.730 --> 05:31.700
She said she thought it was a weasel.

05:34.200 --> 05:36.910
Does it say if she got away with it?

05:36.920 --> 05:38.400
Oh, no. It doesn't matter.

05:38.410 --> 05:40.010
I don't have a garage.

05:42.010 --> 05:43.880
Well, the mug shots are pretty,

05:43.900 --> 05:45.780
but the real crime here is the writing.

05:46.960 --> 05:49.079
Oh, whoa. They're looking for a writer

05:49.080 --> 05:51.180
with copy-editing
experience. I have that.

05:51.320 --> 05:53.440
Yeah, but this is just
sensationalist garbage

05:53.460 --> 05:54.590
anybody could write.

05:54.630 --> 05:57.640
I know. I better get my
résumé together real quick.

05:58.330 --> 06:00.160
Okay, everybody get in here.

06:00.170 --> 06:01.720
I have news.

06:02.080 --> 06:03.850
All right, you're never
gonna believe this,

06:03.950 --> 06:06.620
but I wasn't nauseous at work
because I was hung over...

06:06.690 --> 06:08.020
Dad.

06:10.830 --> 06:12.730
I was sick because...

06:12.790 --> 06:13.930
I'm pregnant!

06:13.940 --> 06:14.950
Aaah!

06:17.200 --> 06:19.770
I can't believe it!

06:19.830 --> 06:21.000
Ohhhh!

06:21.020 --> 06:24.540
Your doctor gave you
less than a 5% chance!

06:24.640 --> 06:27.470
I know, but I had unsafe
sex, and it worked!

06:31.380 --> 06:33.880
You should speak at the high school.

06:34.900 --> 06:36.780
This is a full-on miracle.

06:36.800 --> 06:38.350
You were meant to be a mom.

06:38.420 --> 06:41.160
The doctor said that you were
too old and too pickled...

06:43.360 --> 06:47.130
... but God filled
that uterus with life.

06:48.740 --> 06:51.740
He didn't say "pickled."
Darlene said that.

06:53.000 --> 06:54.670
Oh, yeah, that was one of mine.

06:58.680 --> 07:00.580
We got to celebrate this now,

07:00.690 --> 07:01.879
'cause once the baby comes,

07:01.880 --> 07:03.689
you won't get a moment's peace.

07:03.690 --> 07:04.989
I had had to go to Afghanistan

07:04.990 --> 07:06.590
just to get a decent night's sleep.

07:08.820 --> 07:10.830
Mary thought she was always gonna
be the baby of the family.

07:10.850 --> 07:13.480
She's gonna learn what
every Conner learns...

07:13.550 --> 07:14.720
no one is special.

07:14.770 --> 07:15.820
Mm.

07:17.140 --> 07:18.220
To Becky.

07:18.290 --> 07:20.550
I think I speak for everyone when I say

07:20.560 --> 07:23.060
we can't wait to see how this plays out.

07:25.460 --> 07:27.260
God, I wish Mom was here.

07:27.700 --> 07:29.530
She would be so excited.

07:29.640 --> 07:31.000
She knows.

07:31.060 --> 07:33.660
So, you gonna tell us? Who's the father?

07:33.670 --> 07:34.940
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

07:35.040 --> 07:36.410
Whoa!

07:36.480 --> 07:38.000
Privacy, people.

07:38.010 --> 07:40.780
This is Becky's business
and nobody else.

07:44.400 --> 07:47.080
There is a father, biologically.

07:47.100 --> 07:48.400
I'm just not gonna tell him.

07:49.120 --> 07:51.350
I don't need a man to raise my kid.

07:51.420 --> 07:54.390
You know, it's not a crime for
a baby to have two parents.

07:54.460 --> 07:55.799
It's lovely to be independent,

07:55.800 --> 07:57.240
but not if the baby has to suffer

07:57.260 --> 07:59.660
because you don't have
the time or the money

07:59.770 --> 08:01.300
to take care of him properly.

08:01.470 --> 08:04.460
I'm not trying to prove
how independent I am.

08:05.240 --> 08:07.020
There's other reasons
I'm not telling him.

08:07.310 --> 08:08.400
Like what?

08:08.570 --> 08:10.410
Like it was a one-night stand.

08:12.180 --> 08:15.180
Oh. Well, let's check the Becky board.

08:16.250 --> 08:17.510
Number-one answer?

08:17.620 --> 08:19.480
Ding! "One-night stand."

08:22.350 --> 08:25.460
I'm just saying, I don't have
a relationship with the guy.

08:25.520 --> 08:27.740
He's a stranger, and I'm not gonna have

08:27.760 --> 08:29.860
a stranger telling me
how to raise my kid.

08:29.960 --> 08:31.290
He's still the father.

08:31.400 --> 08:33.559
The father has a right to know.

08:33.600 --> 08:36.100
And you're gonna need help with money.

08:36.169 --> 08:37.830
I got to let you go.

08:37.940 --> 08:39.740
You can't do drywall
when you're pregnant.

08:39.809 --> 08:41.870
Why not? Pregnant women
work all the time.

08:41.940 --> 08:43.150
Not on construction sites.

08:43.159 --> 08:46.120
They're dangerous and full
of all kinds of toxic stuff.

08:47.010 --> 08:49.080
You know how many babies
I've had to let go?

08:51.020 --> 08:53.320
And they always cry.

08:55.400 --> 08:56.990
So you're firing me?

08:57.000 --> 08:58.500
I really need the money.

08:58.680 --> 09:00.860
You can come back when
you have the baby.

09:02.100 --> 09:03.180
Wow.

09:03.200 --> 09:05.999
I wasn't looking for support
from the baby's father,

09:06.000 --> 09:08.800
but I thought I might get
some from my family.

09:11.380 --> 09:13.570
Where would she get that idea?

09:19.980 --> 09:22.200
Sorry. I didn't see a receptionist.

09:22.320 --> 09:24.350
People kept mistaking us
for The New York Times,

09:24.400 --> 09:25.980
so I had to let her go.

09:27.390 --> 09:29.040
Hey, I don't care how small it is.

09:29.050 --> 09:31.640
The fact that anything's being
published in Lanford at all

09:31.660 --> 09:32.660
is pretty sweet.

09:32.760 --> 09:34.460
I'm here about the job.

09:34.530 --> 09:36.260
Oh.

09:36.300 --> 09:39.000
Nice to meet you... Darlene Conner.

09:39.020 --> 09:40.320
Ben.

09:40.380 --> 09:41.606
If you turn out not to be a nut,

09:41.630 --> 09:43.300
I'll tell you my last name.

09:45.260 --> 09:48.580
Um, "waitress at the casino," huh?

09:48.810 --> 09:50.960
Humble brag.

09:52.710 --> 09:54.880
Why'd you leave the job
writing ad copy in Chicago?

09:55.180 --> 09:58.460
Oh, um, it was a combination of things.

09:58.580 --> 10:00.780
I hated the job, they paid nothing,

10:00.820 --> 10:02.920
and then they fired me...
that was the last straw.

10:04.160 --> 10:05.490
Why'd they fire you?

10:05.560 --> 10:07.040
They started using freelancers.

10:07.060 --> 10:08.540
But it worked out because
I had to come back

10:08.560 --> 10:09.570
to help my dad anyway.

10:09.590 --> 10:11.590
So this job would be perfect for me,

10:11.700 --> 10:15.000
and... and honestly, I think
I would be perfect for you

10:15.070 --> 10:16.500
because your paper right now

10:16.570 --> 10:18.470
is just full of a lot of dry facts,

10:18.540 --> 10:20.170
and I think that I could really make

10:20.180 --> 10:22.940
the arsonists and carjackers
people you want to know.

10:27.220 --> 10:28.240
No.

10:29.700 --> 10:32.020
People read this paper to see mug shots,

10:32.040 --> 10:33.849
find out who beat,
stabbed, or robbed who,

10:33.850 --> 10:35.520
and if they live next door.

10:35.590 --> 10:38.220
Oh, and if it's a relative, you know.

10:38.250 --> 10:40.620
Everybody likes to see an
in-law get taken down.

10:42.180 --> 10:44.730
Okay, cool, so, why don't
we take what you're doing

10:44.760 --> 10:46.380
and use that as a jumping-off place?

10:46.960 --> 10:50.070
Or we do what we're doing
and keep doing it.

10:51.720 --> 10:52.800
I get it.

10:52.820 --> 10:55.240
Go slow, don't freak the readers out...

10:55.310 --> 10:56.710
small changes first.

10:56.810 --> 10:59.820
Mm-hmm, mm-hmm. Or no changes,

11:00.150 --> 11:02.950
and then later...

11:03.010 --> 11:05.440
no changes.

11:06.580 --> 11:08.950
Oh, yeah. Okay. I hear you. I hear you.

11:09.020 --> 11:10.820
Deepen the story, but just a little

11:10.840 --> 11:12.720
until you see how much
better you like it.

11:13.680 --> 11:17.790
Or you do it precisely as I
say, and you can keep your job.

11:19.180 --> 11:20.960
Wait. Did you just hire me?

11:22.240 --> 11:23.470
Yes.

11:23.540 --> 11:24.760
Oh, and the pay sucks.

11:24.840 --> 11:27.300
- Ah, thank you!
- Yeah.

11:28.160 --> 11:30.480
That's your office. You
can go home at 6:00.

11:31.380 --> 11:32.940
Uh, I have kids.

11:33.010 --> 11:34.310
Oh. I'm sorry.

11:34.320 --> 11:38.110
Um, you can stay as late as you want.

11:40.950 --> 11:42.650
You know, when I first found out,

11:42.720 --> 11:44.360
I was so excited.

11:44.590 --> 11:48.020
But then I remembered I'm
43, on my own, and broke.

11:48.090 --> 11:49.540
Maybe your dad's right.

11:49.560 --> 11:52.130
Maybe you could bring the
baby's father into the mix,

11:52.230 --> 11:53.960
just to help with expenses.

11:54.070 --> 11:55.570
- Who is it?
- I can't tell you.

11:55.630 --> 11:56.670
All right, I get it.

11:56.770 --> 11:58.530
The sanctity of the intimate act,

11:58.600 --> 12:01.460
the stoic silence between lovers.

12:01.660 --> 12:04.200
No, I mean I don't know
who the hell it is.

12:05.600 --> 12:09.280
It's either Ramon, the manager,
or Emilio, the busboy.

12:09.380 --> 12:11.410
O-Oh, okay.

12:11.480 --> 12:13.960
A very mature, modern dilemma.

12:14.000 --> 12:17.140
Like many of our most
popular romantic comedies,

12:17.190 --> 12:19.490
but with much-needed diversity.

12:20.660 --> 12:23.330
Well, Ramon's the manager.

12:23.400 --> 12:25.300
Is it wrong to tell him he's the father

12:25.360 --> 12:27.000
just because he's in a better position

12:27.070 --> 12:29.270
to shell out a few bucks
to help with the baby?

12:29.330 --> 12:31.980
You are a mother. You do
what's best for the baby.

12:32.140 --> 12:33.470
Go, Ramon!

12:35.940 --> 12:38.300
Um, Ramon?

12:38.360 --> 12:40.910
The Sprite's low on CO2.

12:40.980 --> 12:43.920
Also, hey, I'm pregnant,
and you're the father.

12:45.020 --> 12:47.580
I know because I haven't
been with any other men.

12:47.680 --> 12:49.240
It's not mine.

12:49.420 --> 12:50.840
Normal reaction.

12:50.940 --> 12:53.320
No one feels it can happen to them.

12:53.460 --> 12:55.360
But here we are.

12:55.430 --> 12:57.040
And I'm sure you'll do the right thing

12:57.060 --> 12:58.540
by helping me financially.

12:58.730 --> 13:00.030
I had a vasectomy.

13:00.900 --> 13:03.840
Ironically, that used
to be music to my ears.

13:06.940 --> 13:09.240
I assume I'm working
holidays for a while.

13:12.610 --> 13:13.680
It's the busboy.

13:13.780 --> 13:15.350
Ohhh!

13:15.410 --> 13:16.820
Well, think!

13:16.860 --> 13:18.656
There's got to be somebody
else you slept with

13:18.680 --> 13:20.560
that's got money.

13:20.580 --> 13:22.719
Hey. It is told to me,

13:22.720 --> 13:25.820
um, you have my baby?

13:25.840 --> 13:27.140
Who told you that?

13:27.390 --> 13:28.520
Ramon.

13:28.590 --> 13:30.660
He said it is me.

13:30.720 --> 13:32.460
This is gonna get complicated.

13:32.560 --> 13:34.060
Could you help me out?

13:34.130 --> 13:36.270
The only thing I know how
to say in Spanish is "Yes."

13:36.300 --> 13:38.400
Yeah, I figured that out.

13:40.760 --> 13:43.240
Just tell him the truth.

