And three margaritas.

15:30.440 --> 15:32.180
Throw in a margarita for yourself.

15:33.980 --> 15:35.080
Are you okay?

15:36.680 --> 15:38.820
I'm experiencing a miracle.

15:38.920 --> 15:40.540
It's a very small gesture.

15:40.550 --> 15:42.750
It's like $2, and they're mostly ice.

15:44.770 --> 15:46.600
I can't drink. I'm pregnant.

15:46.990 --> 15:49.919
Becky! I'm so happy for you!

15:49.920 --> 15:51.099
You should be happy.

15:51.100 --> 15:52.380
We've been trying for years,

15:52.400 --> 15:54.400
but Maria has a tilted uterus,

15:54.430 --> 15:56.030
and I'm shooting blanks.

15:57.000 --> 16:00.110
I don't know if I can afford this baby.

16:00.170 --> 16:04.740
I just lost my second
job, the dad can't help,

16:04.810 --> 16:07.320
and...

16:07.420 --> 16:09.080
... I just...

16:09.380 --> 16:12.180
Oh, honey, it's gonna be okay.

16:12.450 --> 16:13.950
Thanks, guys.

16:14.020 --> 16:15.720
Let me get you your drinks.

16:19.120 --> 16:21.340
This might sound kind of cold,

16:21.360 --> 16:22.930
but I want her baby.

16:24.140 --> 16:27.030
Maria, we're not dingoes.

16:27.050 --> 16:29.120
But Becky might be the perfect person.

16:29.140 --> 16:31.140
I mean, we know her, she knows us.

16:31.200 --> 16:33.150
She could even still be
involved in the baby's life.

16:33.170 --> 16:34.810
It's good for everybody.

16:34.880 --> 16:38.640
It's a huge decision for us
that we shouldn't take lightly.

16:38.710 --> 16:41.080
Let me pound some margaritas,
and we'll talk about it.

16:42.820 --> 16:44.880
It's a little rough, but check it out.

16:46.150 --> 16:50.050
"Driven by years of closed doors
and systematic oppression,

16:50.120 --> 16:53.640
Eddie Ray Garrett lunged at
the gas station cashier,

16:53.660 --> 16:55.620
who ended Eddie's career of crime

16:55.640 --> 16:57.060
with a full...

16:57.130 --> 16:59.760
UNICEF can to the temple."

17:02.020 --> 17:03.980
The title is "Give Till It Hurts."

17:04.000 --> 17:05.660
Pretty great, right?

17:05.940 --> 17:07.619
No!

17:07.940 --> 17:09.040
Very great?

17:10.319 --> 17:12.680
You have overestimated

17:12.710 --> 17:14.440
the reading level of our audience.

17:14.460 --> 17:15.800
Okay? Uh...

17:15.819 --> 17:17.900
- You ever seen "Frankenstein"?
- Yeah.

17:17.920 --> 17:20.490
Okay, that's the reading
level of our audience.

17:21.760 --> 17:23.720
And not the doctor... the creature.

17:24.819 --> 17:28.540
I'll give you till "he
lunged at the cashier,"

17:28.560 --> 17:30.180
but then we're out.

17:30.430 --> 17:32.399
Okay, but let's just say

17:32.400 --> 17:35.500
we raise the quality of the writing.

17:35.570 --> 17:37.570
Then we get the doctor and the creature,

17:37.640 --> 17:39.270
and we increase our ad revenue.

17:39.340 --> 17:41.210
Look.

17:41.270 --> 17:43.240
You're clearly intelligent

17:43.310 --> 17:47.340
and have an... obnoxious
kind of integrity.

17:48.660 --> 17:51.750
That is dangerously
close to a compliment.

17:51.850 --> 17:53.880
Well, you can consider
it one if you want.

17:53.890 --> 17:55.690
It wasn't meant that way.

17:56.620 --> 18:01.700
And you are remarkably
stubborn and self-sabotaging.

18:02.820 --> 18:05.200
I was wondering when
you were gonna notice.

18:07.460 --> 18:11.240
Seriously, you've built
something great here.

18:11.340 --> 18:14.110
It's fascinating, it's macabre.

18:14.210 --> 18:15.650
But you just haven't even started

18:15.680 --> 18:17.780
to exploit it properly yet.

18:23.050 --> 18:24.920
That's where I keep my paper clips.

18:27.120 --> 18:29.140
And a dead moth, apparently.

18:30.880 --> 18:33.060
Look, here's the thing.

18:33.160 --> 18:35.930
The colorful writing is just the start.

18:36.000 --> 18:37.880
There is so much more we can do here.

18:38.920 --> 18:41.330
For example, I can
create a website for us.

18:41.370 --> 18:43.660
That's a great way to
attract younger readers.

18:43.940 --> 18:46.050
You know how to create a website?

18:46.080 --> 18:49.240
I do. I can have it up and
running in two weeks.

18:51.080 --> 18:52.540
Okay.

18:52.650 --> 18:54.450
Here's what I'll do.

18:54.510 --> 18:56.750
You are now the managing editor

18:56.780 --> 18:59.580
in charge of our new
Internet Department.

19:00.000 --> 19:01.720
And...

19:01.790 --> 19:04.800
And you get 10% of all
the income you generate.

19:04.990 --> 19:06.850
Oh. And I have complete
creative control.

19:06.890 --> 19:08.560
Not even close.

19:10.760 --> 19:12.300
Hey, let's celebrate, huh?

19:12.400 --> 19:13.700
Dinner's on me.

19:14.630 --> 19:16.580
Desperate and hungry,

19:16.600 --> 19:18.970
he... lunged for his phone.

19:21.420 --> 19:22.430
Okay.

19:23.680 --> 19:25.300
Now you're just being a jerk.

19:26.750 --> 19:28.600
Oh, it's busy.

19:28.660 --> 19:29.920
Well, I think I speak

19:29.940 --> 19:31.719
for everyone in the Internet Department

19:31.720 --> 19:34.090
when I say I think we
can go out for dinner.

19:34.190 --> 19:35.420
What do you like?

19:35.520 --> 19:37.080
Uh, Chinese?

19:37.180 --> 19:39.060
I could go for some shrimp fried rice.

19:40.760 --> 19:42.730
Um...

19:45.060 --> 19:47.530
You probably... You
probably don't know this.

19:47.630 --> 19:50.850
Uh, most of the shrimp we eat
isn't processed ethically,

19:50.860 --> 19:52.540
so you don't want to get that.

19:53.310 --> 19:55.010
Ohhh.

19:55.110 --> 19:56.390
You're confused.

19:56.410 --> 19:58.140
You thought I was a child,

19:58.180 --> 20:01.010
when I'm actually a grown-ass adult.

20:04.220 --> 20:07.440
Yeah. I-I didn't mean to push.
That's not who I am.

20:07.450 --> 20:08.490
Oh, great.

20:10.190 --> 20:11.190
Let's go.

20:13.100 --> 20:14.830
Hope you like 'em thick.

20:14.860 --> 20:17.160
I just about burned out the motor.

20:22.100 --> 20:23.670
We're gonna need spoons.

20:26.270 --> 20:27.760
So, when you and Mom found out

20:27.770 --> 20:29.459
you were gonna have
me, did you freak out?

20:29.460 --> 20:30.479
Only a little.

20:30.480 --> 20:33.060
We didn't know how bad
you were gonna turn out.

20:34.260 --> 20:36.680
The truth is, I remember thinking,

20:36.780 --> 20:39.320
"Oh, my God. I got to be a grown-up now.

20:39.420 --> 20:44.060
I got to buy life insurance,
mutual funds, save for college."

20:44.120 --> 20:47.890
But after a couple of years,
that panic goes away.

20:47.990 --> 20:49.660
And you just forget about that stuff.

20:52.330 --> 20:54.530
At least you had Mom
to go through it with.

20:54.630 --> 20:55.900
Yeah.

20:56.300 --> 20:58.509
Two parents isn't the worst
thing in the world to have.

20:58.510 --> 21:00.470
Just doing milkshakes now, Dad.

